1
00:00:42,850 --> 00:00:48,540
♪Flower petals have fallen,
piling as high as mortal mercilessness♪

2
00:00:49,700 --> 00:00:55,410
♪Gone with the wind,
as if it has never existed♪

3
00:00:56,530 --> 00:00:59,960
♪I ask for more time♪

4
00:01:00,900 --> 00:01:03,290
♪To rewrite our stories♪

5
00:01:03,520 --> 00:01:09,650
♪We travel together in joys and woes♪

6
00:01:10,180 --> 00:01:16,470
♪Blood bathes this entangled destiny♪

7
00:01:17,110 --> 00:01:23,260
♪For the next reunion
in the troubled times♪

8
00:01:24,080 --> 00:01:27,380
♪We tread a treacherous path♪

9
00:01:28,300 --> 00:01:30,640
♪To find each other♪

10
00:01:30,920 --> 00:01:37,600
♪Wars and bleakness,
the bright moon shines upon the city♪

11
00:01:37,600 --> 00:01:40,930
♪I will offer my bravery♪

12
00:01:41,190 --> 00:01:44,380
♪Fighting relentlessly♪

13
00:01:44,660 --> 00:01:47,630
♪All for no regrets♪

14
00:01:47,708 --> 00:01:51,348
♪In this life-and-death battle,
I will not back down♪

15
00:01:51,460 --> 00:01:54,910
♪Withstand enduring time♪

16
00:01:54,910 --> 00:01:58,130
♪Someone at the end of the world
never leaves♪

17
00:01:58,270 --> 00:02:05,210
♪I brave the grim haze
to be with you once again♪

18
00:02:05,210 --> 00:02:10,950
=Love of Nirvana=
(Based on Xiao Lou's novel of the same name)

19
00:02:11,190 --> 00:02:14,180
=Episode 15=

20
00:02:15,880 --> 00:02:17,280
The military equipment case

21
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:18,410
may

22
00:02:18,870 --> 00:02:20,380
be more than just corruption.

23
00:02:23,016 --> 00:02:24,616
What are your thoughts about it,
My Lord?

24
00:02:25,016 --> 00:02:26,088
The military equipment case

25
00:02:26,430 --> 00:02:27,700
was perfect at first.

26
00:02:28,430 --> 00:02:29,780
Why did we find old rice

27
00:02:30,380 --> 00:02:31,930
at this very moment?

28
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:33,200
Following the clues,

29
00:02:33,530 --> 00:02:34,700
we found famine victims.

30
00:02:35,470 --> 00:02:38,040
The famine case is the opening
for the military equipment case.

31
00:02:38,540 --> 00:02:40,530
We also found evidence
of Pei Clan's corruption.

32
00:02:41,600 --> 00:02:42,570
Don't you think

33
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:44,650
everything's going too well?

34
00:02:47,850 --> 00:02:49,260
Do you mean

35
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:51,912
someone is secretly leading us
to investigate the case?

36
00:02:53,224 --> 00:02:55,030
Who is the person
secretly planning all this?

37
00:02:55,430 --> 00:02:56,590
Does Pei Yan know?

38
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:59,130
When it comes to Pei Clan,

39
00:02:59,880 --> 00:03:01,690
even Pei Yan might not see it clearly.

40
00:03:03,430 --> 00:03:04,280
But Pei Yan

41
00:03:04,880 --> 00:03:06,250
won't let it go so easily.

42
00:03:07,540 --> 00:03:08,260
No wonder Pei Yan

43
00:03:08,260 --> 00:03:10,100
neglected the Yan Sisters lately.

44
00:03:10,690 --> 00:03:11,160
Yifei.

45
00:03:11,672 --> 00:03:13,368
Check the abandoned
houses in the suburbs

46
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:14,360
and the shoe prints.

47
00:03:14,630 --> 00:03:16,380
Don't let go of any clues

48
00:03:16,750 --> 00:03:17,660
related to the Yans.

49
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:18,904
Yes, Your Lordship.

50
00:03:33,850 --> 00:03:34,940
(Pei Clan)

51
00:03:35,040 --> 00:03:36,820
(will)

52
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:38,130
temporarily

53
00:03:38,470 --> 00:03:40,700
give you and your son a place to stay.

54
00:03:41,660 --> 00:03:42,250
However,

55
00:03:43,080 --> 00:03:44,660
you must follow the rules all the more

56
00:03:44,910 --> 00:03:46,760
when staying with others.

57
00:03:47,690 --> 00:03:48,370
Don't have

58
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:51,470
ideas that you shouldn't have.

59
00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:10,880
Yan.

60
00:04:12,780 --> 00:04:14,000
Look at me.

61
00:04:16,640 --> 00:04:18,340
Remember everything that happened today.

62
00:04:20,250 --> 00:04:22,000
Remember these people's attitudes.

63
00:04:24,310 --> 00:04:26,230
Only when you are strong enough

64
00:04:27,750 --> 00:04:30,230
can you make others submit to you.

65
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:32,750
Otherwise,

66
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:36,630
you'll always
be someone else's stepping stone

67
00:04:38,840 --> 00:04:40,070
and have nothing.

68
00:04:41,208 --> 00:04:42,370
Have you kept that in mind?

69
00:04:46,260 --> 00:04:47,050
Answer me.

70
00:04:48,024 --> 00:04:48,940
I've kept it in mind.

71
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:50,640
Louder.

72
00:04:51,240 --> 00:04:52,130
I've kept it in mind.

73
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:53,310
Louder!

74
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:55,020
(I've kept it in mind!)

75
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:17,304
There were too many things going on

76
00:05:17,352 --> 00:05:18,600
last night that I neglected you.

77
00:05:19,310 --> 00:05:20,440
Are you okay?

78
00:05:21,640 --> 00:05:22,670
Don't worry, Your Lordship.

79
00:05:22,870 --> 00:05:23,760
I'm all right.

80
00:05:25,550 --> 00:05:26,690
Don't be self-willed again.

81
00:05:26,940 --> 00:05:27,940
Protect yourself.

82
00:05:28,280 --> 00:05:30,216
This isn't something
you should get involved in.

83
00:05:32,190 --> 00:05:33,580
I've troubled you.

84
00:05:35,020 --> 00:05:35,750
I know

85
00:05:36,080 --> 00:05:37,500
you want to feed the famine victims.

86
00:05:38,020 --> 00:05:39,190
I'll write you an edict.

87
00:05:39,640 --> 00:05:41,752
Go to Pei Clan's granary
to take out some food

88
00:05:41,870 --> 00:05:42,960
and send the food to them.

89
00:05:43,310 --> 00:05:44,250
I'll take care

90
00:05:44,580 --> 00:05:45,460
of the rest.

91
00:05:48,080 --> 00:05:49,170
Thank you, Your Lordship.

92
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:51,810
From now on,

93
00:05:52,070 --> 00:05:53,460
just stay by my side.

94
00:05:53,730 --> 00:05:54,820
After this busy period,

95
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:57,140
I'll travel south with you
to go sightseeing.

96
00:05:58,500 --> 00:06:00,700
Are you really
interested in sightseeing?

97
00:06:03,384 --> 00:06:04,750
All that matters is you're happy.

98
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,080
We can talk about this

99
00:06:08,430 --> 00:06:09,670
later.

100
00:06:14,950 --> 00:06:17,570
(Nanling, Pei Clan's Granary)

101
00:06:22,170 --> 00:06:22,790
Bring them over.

102
00:06:33,460 --> 00:06:33,940
Be careful.

103
00:06:35,380 --> 00:06:35,930
All right.

104
00:06:36,250 --> 00:06:37,070
You can go now.

105
00:06:37,256 --> 00:06:39,000
But there are
only two bags of rice here.

106
00:06:39,190 --> 00:06:41,020
The edict clearly writes
five dan of grain.

107
00:06:41,610 --> 00:06:42,670
Take it or leave it.

108
00:06:42,900 --> 00:06:44,130
If you don't want it, get lost.

109
00:06:44,250 --> 00:06:45,290
What's with you?

110
00:06:47,670 --> 00:06:48,870
These people are hateful

111
00:06:48,870 --> 00:06:49,820
for feigning compliance.

112
00:06:50,856 --> 00:06:52,110
It's what food given out of pity

113
00:06:52,670 --> 00:06:53,520
is like.

114
00:06:55,930 --> 00:06:56,700
Ci.

115
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:59,190
If you want to help
those famine victims,

116
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:01,080
these two bags of rice aren't enough.

117
00:07:02,870 --> 00:07:03,440
Ziming.

118
00:07:03,900 --> 00:07:05,130
Go to the deserted temple

119
00:07:05,130 --> 00:07:07,240
and give porridge and medicine
to those famine victims.

120
00:07:07,250 --> 00:07:09,110
I'll figure out the rest.

121
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:18,260
Miss Jiang.

122
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:19,310
Ayan.

123
00:07:19,370 --> 00:07:20,600
Are you going out on the boat?

124
00:07:20,930 --> 00:07:22,630
I want to get some food in the river.

125
00:07:23,110 --> 00:07:25,170
It's hard to catch fish
at this time of year.

126
00:07:25,750 --> 00:07:26,870
If I can't catch any fish,

127
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:28,730
I can always catch something else.

128
00:07:29,690 --> 00:07:31,320
If you want to help famine victims,

129
00:07:31,380 --> 00:07:32,630
why not seek help from Lord?

130
00:07:33,310 --> 00:07:35,190
If I rely on others for everything,

131
00:07:35,250 --> 00:07:36,984
I'll never be able
to solve any problems.

132
00:07:38,260 --> 00:07:39,050
Let me help you.

133
00:07:45,370 --> 00:07:46,230
Young Master.

134
00:07:47,260 --> 00:07:48,640
Young Master, taste it.

135
00:07:50,500 --> 00:07:51,050
Young Master.

136
00:07:51,440 --> 00:07:52,020
Young Master.

137
00:07:52,340 --> 00:07:53,050
Young Master.

138
00:07:54,250 --> 00:07:54,750
Speak.

139
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:56,880
Pei Yan's maid,
who exposed our whereabouts,

140
00:07:56,940 --> 00:07:58,310
is out on a boat alone.

141
00:08:02,430 --> 00:08:04,130
Father worked so hard for Pei Clan

142
00:08:04,130 --> 00:08:05,460
but suffered so much.

143
00:08:08,080 --> 00:08:10,200
I want to get justice for him.

144
00:08:12,940 --> 00:08:13,380
Here.

145
00:08:15,690 --> 00:08:17,610
Miss Jiang, you're amazing.

146
00:08:18,170 --> 00:08:19,820
It's Nanling river that's amazing.

147
00:08:21,790 --> 00:08:23,170
But is this edible?

148
00:08:23,690 --> 00:08:25,230
I read it in a medical book.

149
00:08:25,570 --> 00:08:27,080
It's called bitterweed.

150
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:29,048
You can eat it
after boiling it in water.

151
00:08:29,050 --> 00:08:30,000
You can add some seasoning

152
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:30,870
or make it a salad.

153
00:08:31,170 --> 00:08:32,700
Although it's not as delicious as rice,

154
00:08:32,820 --> 00:08:34,620
it can fill your stomach for a while.

155
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:36,170
Nanling's famine victims

156
00:08:36,170 --> 00:08:38,080
should really thank you and Lord.

157
00:08:39,270 --> 00:08:41,390
Lord placed righteousness above family.

158
00:08:41,860 --> 00:08:43,190
He should be

159
00:08:43,190 --> 00:08:44,720
someone trustworthy.

160
00:08:57,688 --> 00:08:58,310
Young Master.

161
00:09:00,650 --> 00:09:02,070
You're just a maid,

162
00:09:02,070 --> 00:09:03,530
but you're quite fiery.

163
00:09:04,440 --> 00:09:05,310
What are you doing?

164
00:09:05,790 --> 00:09:07,670
I suspect you're harboring criminals.

165
00:09:07,912 --> 00:09:08,940
I want to search the boat.

166
00:09:09,688 --> 00:09:10,696
Our boat is so small

167
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:12,200
that you can see everything at a glance.

168
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:13,570
I think you're here to cause trouble.

169
00:09:13,570 --> 00:09:14,650
So what if I am?

170
00:09:15,270 --> 00:09:16,960
If you hadn't interfered,

171
00:09:17,768 --> 00:09:19,310
my father wouldn't end up this way now.

172
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:22,030
What are you waiting for?

173
00:09:22,270 --> 00:09:22,740
Search them.

174
00:09:28,820 --> 00:09:29,740
Losers.

175
00:09:30,650 --> 00:09:31,940
You're nosy, aren't you?

176
00:09:32,310 --> 00:09:32,740
Okay.

177
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:35,270
I'll throw you into the lake
and feed you to the fish today.

178
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:48,290
Young Master.

179
00:09:48,790 --> 00:09:49,740
We're no match for him.

180
00:09:49,896 --> 00:09:51,128
We should heal our wounds first.

181
00:10:00,860 --> 00:10:01,700
Ayan.

182
00:10:02,150 --> 00:10:03,290
Go home first.

183
00:10:16,820 --> 00:10:17,740
Thank you.

184
00:10:18,808 --> 00:10:20,536
I'm just
fighting violence with violence.

185
00:10:21,550 --> 00:10:23,170
This is the third time you've saved me.

186
00:10:23,790 --> 00:10:24,790
The first time

187
00:10:25,010 --> 00:10:26,570
was in the county jail.

188
00:10:27,064 --> 00:10:29,640
The second time was
in the dry well at the deserted temple.

189
00:10:30,050 --> 00:10:31,120
This is the third time.

190
00:10:33,570 --> 00:10:35,290
If you want to thank me,

191
00:10:35,860 --> 00:10:37,120
why not just submit to me

192
00:10:39,430 --> 00:10:40,790
and be my spy?

193
00:10:42,910 --> 00:10:44,340
I didn't finish talking.

194
00:10:44,392 --> 00:10:45,880
You tried killing me three times

195
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:46,860
and saved me three times.

196
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:48,320
We're even.

197
00:10:54,970 --> 00:10:56,650
(Jiyun Temple)

198
00:11:07,620 --> 00:11:08,390
Miss Jiang.

199
00:11:09,190 --> 00:11:09,790
What's wrong?

200
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:13,120
Let's cook the porridge
and dishes separately.

201
00:11:13,460 --> 00:11:14,220
Why?

202
00:11:15,530 --> 00:11:17,620
I'm just used to separating

203
00:11:17,790 --> 00:11:18,510
rice and dishes.

204
00:11:18,920 --> 00:11:20,170
How about I do it instead?

205
00:11:20,340 --> 00:11:20,810
Sure.

206
00:11:43,460 --> 00:11:44,200
Commander.

207
00:11:44,890 --> 00:11:46,430
Can I borrow your rock sugar?

208
00:11:48,620 --> 00:11:49,740
What's that?

209
00:11:50,860 --> 00:11:52,100
It's

210
00:11:52,740 --> 00:11:55,010
what you used to tease me

211
00:11:55,010 --> 00:11:56,240
by breaking my kite.

212
00:11:59,864 --> 00:12:01,624
Do you want me
to give you another example?

213
00:12:43,340 --> 00:12:43,810
Here.

214
00:12:44,328 --> 00:12:45,270
Have some porridge.

215
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:51,980
Miss.

216
00:12:53,720 --> 00:12:55,220
I want meat.

217
00:12:56,550 --> 00:12:56,940
Be good.

218
00:12:57,270 --> 00:12:58,248
Have some porridge first.

219
00:12:58,860 --> 00:12:59,320
Here.

220
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:03,030
How about I teach you a trick?

221
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:05,820
Close your eyes with me.

222
00:13:07,890 --> 00:13:09,820
Imagine that in front of you

223
00:13:10,170 --> 00:13:13,030
is a bowl of steaming

224
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:17,440
and fragrant braised beef.

225
00:13:17,960 --> 00:13:18,980
Take a bite

226
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:21,550
and the taste lingers in your mouth.

227
00:13:22,050 --> 00:13:23,190
Chew it

228
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:24,940
and it's smooth and chewy.

229
00:13:25,320 --> 00:13:26,840
At this time,

230
00:13:27,010 --> 00:13:30,030
what goes best with braised beef

231
00:13:30,150 --> 00:13:34,100
is this bowl of delicious hot porridge.

232
00:13:38,720 --> 00:13:39,600
Drink slowly.

233
00:13:39,700 --> 00:13:40,340
Is it good?

234
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:41,720
Yes.

235
00:13:42,770 --> 00:13:43,550
Drink more. Here.

236
00:13:55,390 --> 00:13:55,720
Here.

237
00:14:04,700 --> 00:14:05,340
Taste it.

238
00:14:09,570 --> 00:14:11,070
I added sugar.

239
00:14:11,150 --> 00:14:12,030
Try it.

240
00:14:13,940 --> 00:14:14,860
Try it.

241
00:14:25,770 --> 00:14:26,600
Do you think

242
00:14:27,070 --> 00:14:28,460
treating them to a bowl of porridge

243
00:14:29,070 --> 00:14:30,650
will solve their problems?

244
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:33,190
I know it's impossible,

245
00:14:33,940 --> 00:14:35,430
but I'll think of a solution.

246
00:14:38,030 --> 00:14:39,170
Do you want to try

247
00:14:39,820 --> 00:14:41,240
fighting violence with violence?

248
00:14:46,740 --> 00:14:47,770
Bottoms up.

249
00:14:58,530 --> 00:14:59,620
How come it's you again?

250
00:15:00,150 --> 00:15:01,620
We'll give you ten minutes.

251
00:15:01,624 --> 00:15:02,648
Send five dan of grains

252
00:15:02,680 --> 00:15:03,360
and 50 jin of meat

253
00:15:03,370 --> 00:15:05,176
to the deserted temple
in the west of the city.

254
00:15:06,570 --> 00:15:07,860
How dare you make trouble here?

255
00:15:08,510 --> 00:15:09,320
Boys.

256
00:15:10,010 --> 00:15:10,980
Get your weapons

257
00:15:11,128 --> 00:15:11,690
and get them.

258
00:15:17,290 --> 00:15:18,070
Attack!

259
00:15:41,290 --> 00:15:42,170
Your head is fine.

260
00:15:42,270 --> 00:15:43,080
Open your eyes.

261
00:15:50,620 --> 00:15:51,890
Do you know who he is?

262
00:15:52,264 --> 00:15:54,440
Even the king of hell will run
when he sees him.

263
00:15:54,650 --> 00:15:56,580
He's Guangming Bureau's
Commander Wei Zhao.

264
00:15:56,940 --> 00:15:58,360
Hurry and prepare five dan of grains

265
00:15:58,360 --> 00:15:59,190
and 50 jin of meat.

266
00:16:00,340 --> 00:16:02,650
So what
if he's Guangming Bureau's commander?

267
00:16:03,310 --> 00:16:05,310
How dare you offend Nanling's Pei Clan?

268
00:16:05,720 --> 00:16:07,650
You guys are really bold.

269
00:16:08,856 --> 00:16:10,810
You bully others
by taking advantage of your power.

270
00:16:10,904 --> 00:16:12,632
And you bully the weak
and fear the strong.

271
00:16:12,632 --> 00:16:13,624
You're worse than animals.

272
00:16:13,624 --> 00:16:14,720
I'll cut your flesh

273
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:16,070
and drain your blood.

274
00:16:16,530 --> 00:16:17,690
What can you do to me?

275
00:16:18,580 --> 00:16:20,290
Please spare me, Lord Wei.

276
00:16:20,290 --> 00:16:21,580
Miss Jiang is easily persuaded.

277
00:16:21,890 --> 00:16:24,070
I hate bargaining the most.

278
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:27,310
I asked you to open up the granary.

279
00:16:27,620 --> 00:16:29,480
I can't do that.

280
00:16:29,770 --> 00:16:31,790
These rice belong to Pei Clan.

281
00:16:31,790 --> 00:16:33,070
Even if I had ten heads,

282
00:16:33,270 --> 00:16:34,340
I wouldn't dare do it.

283
00:16:34,530 --> 00:16:36,340
If Nanling's Pei Clan
has any objections,

284
00:16:36,530 --> 00:16:37,940
ask them to find me at any time.

285
00:16:40,340 --> 00:16:40,840
